"title": "8743: faithlessness, nature and causes of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8743",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The abandoning of a commitment to the Lord, seen in disowning him, wandering from the truth and becoming entangled with the world, and resulting in judgment.</p>\n<h2>Warnings against faithlessness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:12-2Tim2:13\">2TI 2:12–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:33\">MAT 10:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:9\">LUK 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:62\">LUK 9:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:35-Heb10:39\">HEB 10:35–10:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:3-Hab2:4\">HAB 2:3–2:4</a></p>\n<h2>Ways in which faithlessness is seen</h2>\n<h3>Turning away from the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:12\">HEB 3:12</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Abandoning the gospel of grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:6\">GAL 1:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Becoming entangled in the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:20-2Pet2:22\">2PE 2:20–2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:11\">PRO 26:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:10\">2TI 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>Causes of faithlessness</h2>\n<h3>False teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:17-2Tim2:18\">2TI 2:17–2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:7\">GAL 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:8-Gal4:11\">GAL 4:8–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:3\">1TI 4:1–4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:3-2Tim4:4\">2TI 4:3–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:17\">2PE 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>Persecution and trials</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:20-Matt13:21\">MAT 13:20–13:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:16-Mark4:17\">MRK 4:16–4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:13\">LUK 8:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:9-Matt24:13\">MAT 24:9–24:13</a></p>\n<h3>Concern for money and possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:8-Prov30:9\">PRO 30:8–30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:22\">MAT 13:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:18-Mark4:19\">MRK 4:18–4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:14\">LUK 8:14</a></p>\n<h3>Love growing cold</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:12\">MAT 24:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:4\">REV 2:4</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual desire</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:11-1Tim5:15\">1TI 5:11–5:15</a></p>\n<h2>Faithlessness brings punishment</h2>\n<h3>Church discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:18-1Tim1:20\">1TI 1:18–1:20</a> <em>These men had been excluded from the church, a sanctuary from Satan's power.</em></p>\n<h3>God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:33\">MAT 10:33</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:9\">LUK 12:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:4-Heb6:6\">HEB 6:4–6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:26-Heb10:27\">HEB 10:26–10:27</a></p>\n<h2>The faithlessness of those who fall away</h2>\n<h3>The absence of true faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:19\">1JN 2:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>True faith is proved by perseverance</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:2-Jas1:3\">JAS 1:2–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:5-1Pet1:7\">1PE 1:5–1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's faithlessness in the OT</h2>\n<h3>Israel's unfaithfulness led to God's rejection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:56-Ps78:59\">PSA 78:56–78:59</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings not to repeat Israel's unfaithfulness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7-Ps95:11\">PSA 95:7–95:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:7-Heb3:12\">HEB 3:7–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:1-Heb4:2\">HEB 4:1–4:2</a></p>",
